{
  "texts": [
    "Effective Training Strategies.",
    "Researchers have explored different training strategies for pretrained trans-former encoder-based contextualized language models.",
    "For instance, Sentence-BERT (SBERT) [86] uses Siamese and triple networks to generate contextual sentence embeddings.",
    "It uses cosine similarity or the Manhattan/Euclidean distance in the interaction stage to find semantically similar sentences.",
    "SBERT reduces the computational complexity of the system from 𝑛 2 to 𝑛 while ensuring accuracy."
  ]
}